CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 21, 1964, pg. 10 reads: "Post Captains Cited - With a banquet at North Side Lodge recently, members of Mosiwidael Temple Marching Club 38 sponsored a reception in honor of Post Captain Bernice Pickney and present Captain Ellen Crenshaw, seated center. Other guests seated include Mrs. Inez Crenshaw, Elijah Williams, Lucy Coleman, Jimmie L. Floyd, Early Crenshaw, Julius Graham, Mabel Neal, Gen. Edward Miles and PGE Ely Randolph.  Shown standing are (left to right) Mmes. Florence Murray, Alice Rose, Alma Young, Naomi Taylor, Viola Harris, Erma Williams, Dora Lee, Ethel Duke, Sam Gray and Helen Redman. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Honorees Bernice Pickney and Ellen Crenshaw, seated center, and guests seated include: Inez Crenshaw, Elijah Williams, Lucy Coleman, Jimmie L. Floyd, Early Crenshaw, Julius Graham, Mabel Neal, Gen. Edward Miles, and Ely Randolph; standing: Florence Murray, Alice Rose, Alma Young, Naomi Taylor, Viola Harris, Erma Williams, Dora Lee, Ethel Duke, Sam Gray, and Helen Redman, posed behind banquet table in North Side Elks
